This article provides a report on the changes to the legal and policy frameworks for the United States' use of military force and national security operations. It is required by the National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA) for Fiscal Year 2018 and 2020. The report covers the calendar year 2020 and includes a classified annex. Former President Obama issued a similar report in 2016, and former President Trump submitted reports in 2018 and 2020. The report mentions that President Biden submitted a notification in February 2021, describing changes to the legal and policy frameworks. The article also mentions the application of the Authorization for Use of Military Force to specific groups and provides an example of a military strike conducted in Iraq in January 2020, authorized by former President Trump.